						               													<description>N&amp;eacute;cropole is a boardgame designed for 2 to 6 players, and can be played in several mode (teams, competitive or versus a game master).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player take control of up to 3 undead heroes. They can be vampires, necromancers or ghosts.&amp;#10;Each hero is chosen amongst three classes: sorcerer &amp;#226;&amp;#152;&amp;#133;, warrior &amp;#226;&amp;#140;&amp;#189; or assassin &amp;#226;&amp;#152;&amp;#190;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Classes will have great impact within attack phases during fights. They will give your heroes dedicated abilities (all unique).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#140;&amp;#189; Warriors master &amp;quot;talent&amp;quot; to dominate the battlefield.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#152;&amp;#133; Sorcerers are spell casters, specialized in control and area effect damages.&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#152;&amp;#190; Assassins use their skills to make surgical strikes against their preys.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Abilities and legendary artifacts are won by exploring the various Necropole's districts and accomplishing epic quests.&amp;#10;You can also attack your opponents and go into the slummy areas to trade souls for gear.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Possibilities are endless to fulfill your objectives and win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As each card is unique, each game is unique too.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Now is your turn to master the Necropole, city of the dead.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Necropole is an epic game of exploration and skirmish fights.&amp;#10;Players will battle against other undeads (controlled by theor opponents or the game master), using cards in their hands and rolling dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
